{"lemma":"حَمِيمٌ","slug":"حَمِيمٌ","root":"ح.م.م","root_slug":"ح-م-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-م-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حَمِيم","root":"حمم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":20},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n9004"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%85%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"hot water, hot bath, fever","examples":[{"text":"لَهُمْ شَرَابٌ مِنْ حَمِيمٍ وَعَذَابٌ أَلِيمٌ بِمَا كَانُوا يَكْفُرُونَ","english":"For them will be a drink of scalding water and a painful punishment because they used to disbelieve."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"at a fairly or comfortably high temperature"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"close (e.g., friend, associate, confidant), bosom (e.g., buddy)","examples":[{"text":"وَلَا تَسْتَوِي الْحَسَنَةُ وَلَا السَّيِّئَةُ ۚ ادْفَعْ بِالَّتِي هِيَ أَحْسَنُ فَإِذَا الَّذِي بَيْنَكَ وَبَيْنَهُ عَدَاوَةٌ كَأَنَّهُ وَلِيٌّ حَمِيمٌ","english":"And the good deed does not equal the bad: repel by that which is better, whereupon he who is inimical to you will be as if he were a devoted friend."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"warm, friendly, cordial (e.g., relations between two or more parties)"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"intimate, of a sexual nature"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"فَعِيل (faʕīl)-type stative-verb derived from the active participle from the verb حَمَّ (ḥamma)."},"ipa":["/ħa.miːm/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n9004","headword_ar":"حَمِيمٌ","root":"Hm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qayoZ","text_ar":"قَيْظ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"summer:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most vehement heat of summer, from the auroral rising of the Pleiades"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at the epoch of the Flight about the 13th of May O. S."},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the auroral rising of Canopus"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at the same period about the 4th of August O. S."},{"kind":"text","text":"): or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehemence of heat"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a period of about twenty nights, commencing at the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"auroral"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rising of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~abaraAn","text_ar":"الدَّبَرَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at the epoch of the Flight about the 26th of May O. S."},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (AZ, T voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawo'N","text_ar":"نَوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Live coals with which one fumigates."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, Sh.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hot water;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, ISd, Mgh, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamiymapN","text_ar":"حَمِيمَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, ISd, K:) or so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA='N HamiymN","text_ar":"مَا=ءٌ حَمِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamaAy^imu","text_ar":"حَمَايِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) i. e. pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamiymN","text_ar":"حَمِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to IAar; but accord. to ISd, of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamiymapN","text_ar":"حَمِيمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Cold water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cold,"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to water: so, accord. to IAar, in the saying of a poet,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wasaAga liYa Al$~araAbu wakunotu qidomFA\n                      \n                     \n                        A^akaAdu A^agaS~u biAlmaA='i AlHamiymi"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And wine has become easy to swallow to me, whereas I used, in old time, nearly to be choked with cold water"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Az, TA:) thus bearing two contr. significations. (Az, K.) ―         -b5-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rain that comes in the time of vehement heat;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after the heat has become vehement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) because it is hot; (M;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sayof","text_ar":"صَيْف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"summer"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when the ground is hot."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b6-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sweat;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, S, A, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Him~apN","text_ar":"حِمَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Az, A, K:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HumaAmN","text_ar":"حُمَامٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to signify the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sweat of horses."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 92.) One says, (to a person who has been in the bath, A, TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAba Hamiymuka","text_ar":"طَابَ حَمِيمُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAbato Him~atuka","text_ar":"طَابَتْ حِمَّتُكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May thy sweat be good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, A, K;) and consequently,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may God make thy body sound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"healthy:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA:) or the former may mean as above, or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may thy bathing be good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasant:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IB:) one should not say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAba Ham~aAmuka","text_ar":"طَابَ حَمَّامُكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) though MF defends it. (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A relation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for whose case one is anxious"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"solicitous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whom one loves and by whom one is beloved:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an affectionate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a compassionate, relation, who is sharp,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hasty, to protect his kinsfolk:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an object of love; a person beloved:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or a man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brother;"},{"kind":"text","text":"his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"friend,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"true friend;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because anxious, or solicitous, for him: (Ham p. 90:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHim~N","text_ar":"مُحِمٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same: the pl. [of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hmym","text_ar":"حميم"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHim~aA='u","text_ar":"اَحِمَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and sometimes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamiymN","text_ar":"حَمِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as a pl., and as fem.; (K;) as well as sing. and masc. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHamiymu","text_ar":"الحَمِيمُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlHaAjapi","text_ar":"بِالحَاجَةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He who devotes himself to obtain the object of want; who is solicitous for it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"walaA yudoriku AlHaAjaAti A_il~aA HamiymuhaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And none will attain the objects of want but he who devotes himself to obtain them; who is solicitous for them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IAar, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","ISd","Msb","Az","TA","M","A","IB","Lth"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}